
Git: version control system used for tracing changes in source code during development

Gihub: web-based hosting service for your git repositories

need github account credentials to connect git to github

To set git identity on local account

git config --global user.name "your username"
git config --global user.email "mail@example.com"

To create a repository:

cd folder
git init

To add repository documentation:

echo "title_in_markdown_syntax" > README.md

To add files and folders to the repository:

git add folder1
git add file1
...
...

To record changes:

git commit -m "First commit"

To check status of version control:

git status

To check differences b/w file in staging (added files) and files in repository (committed):

(files might need to be added each time they're committed? idk?)

git diff

Branching: allows working on new features in parallel


Push local project to GitHub:

git remote add origin https://github.com/usermae/project.git

To push local repo to GitHub:

git push -u origin master

To remove the origin

git remote remove origin